Bet he'll be there.

256
00:14:24,783 --> 00:14:27,239
- You're not going to first Thursday.
- Why not?

257
00:14:27,239 --> 00:14:30,930
The old timers don't take too kindly to
women crashing their night with the boys.

258
00:14:30,930 --> 00:14:33,119
Too bad. It's a new world.

259
00:14:33,119 --> 00:14:36,040
Those dinosaurs are
bad enough sober, Lilly.

260
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,745
You saying you won't go with me?

261
00:14:37,745 --> 00:14:39,944
I'm saying go see Butch in the morning.

262
00:14:39,944 --> 00:14:42,410
Forget Jones tavern.

263
00:15:04,481 --> 00:15:06,815
Wife know you're on a date tonight?

264
00:15:06,815 --> 00:15:08,090
Hey, Butch.

265
00:15:08,898 --> 00:15:10,931
You know detective Rush.

266
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,265
How you doing, Butch?

267
00:15:12,265 --> 00:15:18,986
This one's for Joe Washington
and all the guys who died on the line.

268
00:15:24,445 --> 00:15:25,765
We got to talk.

269
00:15:25,765 --> 00:15:27,239
Yeah.

270
00:15:27,413 --> 00:15:30,968
Diane called and told me about the crap
you came asking about Joe's money.

271
00:15:30,968 --> 00:15:32,527
There was money going
out of his account.

272
00:15:32,527 --> 00:15:34,014
You know what it was for?

273
00:15:34,014 --> 00:15:35,971
This ain't no place to bring a lady, bro.

274
00:15:35,971 --> 00:15:38,683
- Any ideas about the money, Butch?
- No.

275
00:15:38,683 --> 00:15:41,447
Turns out Washington knew
runner real well.

276
00:15:41,447 --> 00:15:46,321
I hope no one's trying to associate
my fallen partner with some drug dealer.

277
00:15:46,321 --> 00:15:48,075
- How'd he know runner, Butch?
- She thinks she can come in here...

278
00:15:48,075 --> 00:15:49,894
- Just answer the question.
- Smearing a good cop's name...

279
00:15:49,894 --> 00:15:51,327
Hey!

280
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:56,216
I'm the one asking the questions.

281
00:15:56,216 --> 00:16:00,579
So what's your question, detective?

282
00:16:02,434 --> 00:16:05,358
Was Washington paying someone off?

283
00:16:08,228 --> 00:16:10,322
You know who we got here, boys?

284
00:16:10,322 --> 00:16:14,702
The only female in homicide
working cold cases.

285
00:16:14,702 --> 00:16:17,336
- Know why?
- Maybe you ought to sit down, Butch.

286
00:16:17,336 --> 00:16:19,179
'Cause it's in the basement.

287
00:16:19,179 --> 00:16:23,212
Where the little lady can
dust down the files.

288
00:16:41,957 --> 00:16:44,633
So how'd it go at the tavern?

289
00:16:44,798 --> 00:16:47,201
Ass handed to me.

290
00:16:47,650 --> 00:16:49,404
Does that surprise you?

291
00:16:49,404 --> 00:16:53,416
I think Sarreti, the assigned on the case,
suspected the drug angle, too.

292
00:16:53,416 --> 00:16:57,611
An interview Sarreti did
with Deante Rollins, heroin dealer.

293
00:16:57,611 --> 00:17:01,376
His territory was raymond jennings
in the early '70's.

294
00:17:01,376 --> 00:17:04,112
Like Sarreti was wondering
about the cash himself.

295
00:17:04,112 --> 00:17:08,085
But we can't ask him 'cause he keeled
over from a heart attack last year.

296
00:17:08,085 --> 00:17:09,391
And back then,

297
00:17:09,391 --> 00:17:12,374
- Deante wasn't sharing.
- What about now?

298
00:17:12,374 --> 00:17:15,042
Maybe he's learned to play with others.

299
00:17:17,818 --> 00:17:19,914
Never heard of no runner.

300
00:17:19,914 --> 00:17:21,263
You sure about that?

301
00:17:21,263 --> 00:17:24,086
Like I say, never heard of him.

302
00:17:24,086 --> 00:17:26,417
And your word is bond, Deante.

303
00:17:26,417 --> 00:17:28,719
My name is Brother Jamal.

304
00:17:28,719 --> 00:17:29,709
Sure it is.

305
00:17:29,709 --> 00:17:32,177
Asalaam a fakim, my brother.

306
00:17:32,369 --> 00:17:34,551
Like you know what that means.

307
00:17:34,551 --> 00:17:37,239
What does it mean, Jamal?

308
00:17:37,239 --> 00:17:39,437
Peace be with you.

309
00:17:40,251 --> 00:17:42,360
Have you found it yet?

310
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:43,645
Peace?

311
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:45,244
It's a journey.

312
00:17:45,244 --> 00:17:46,801
There is no it.

313
00:17:46,801 --> 00:17:49,079
There is no end.

314
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:52,432
A tough road, redemption.

315
00:17:52,432 --> 00:17:55,160
Yes, especially when you're dealing
smack to women and children.

316
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:58,458
I never sold to children. Ever.

317
00:17:58,458 --> 00:18:00,803
Back in the day, we was businessmen.

318
00:18:00,803 --> 00:18:03,916
Organized, chains of command,

319
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:06,462
none of this teenage gangsta bull today.

320
00:18:06,462 --> 00:18:07,973
- You were disciplined.
- That's right.

321
00:18:07,973 --> 00:18:11,106
Working those basketball courts,
24-seven, 365.

322
00:18:11,106 --> 00:18:12,412
Never missed a day.

323
00:18:12,412 --> 00:18:15,891
So you were there that night
Washington got killed.

324
00:18:18,315 --> 00:18:21,553
And you must have seen the fight.

325
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:25,311
Yeah. I seen it.

326
00:18:25,311 --> 00:18:26,634
You don't own this, man.

327
00:18:26,634 --> 00:18:28,642
Well, I own this. I own you.

328
00:18:28,642 --> 00:18:31,290
I own everything you is, Joe boy.

329
00:18:33,512 --> 00:18:36,297
And the cop runs up into the projects.

330
00:18:39,297 --> 00:18:41,198
What was he doing?

331
00:18:41,198 --> 00:18:44,462
A few minutes later
he comes running back down.

332
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,613
Sam!

333
00:18:50,544 --> 00:18:51,708
Sammy!

334
00:18:52,345 --> 00:18:53,449
Sammy!

335
00:18:53,449 --> 00:18:55,037
Sam!

336
00:18:55,225 --> 00:18:56,558
Sammy!

337
00:18:58,563 --> 00:19:00,647
Where'd Sammy go to?

338
00:19:00,881 --> 00:19:02,314
What about runner?
You seen him?

339
00:19:02,314 --> 00:19:04,050
Where did runner go, huh?!

340
00:19:04,050 --> 00:19:06,327
Took off in some car, man!

341
00:19:06,327 --> 00:19:09,141
Towards the tracks, man!

342
00:19:21,951 --> 00:19:23,363
Who's Sammy?

343
00:19:23,363 --> 00:19:27,444
The reason runner and his homie split
'cause of something that happened to her.

344
00:19:27,444 --> 00:19:28,936
Who was his homie?

345
00:19:28,936 --> 00:19:31,447
All I know is they was tight.

346
00:19:31,447 --> 00:19:35,101
Had the same tattoo on their knuckles.

347
00:19:38,084 --> 00:19:41,299
Here we go.
Joseph Washingtongs autopsy photo.

348
00:19:41,299 --> 00:19:42,307
From the original negative,

349
00:19:42,307 --> 00:19:47,348
I printed onto technical pan film
and transferred onto high contrast slides.

350
00:19:47,348 --> 00:19:49,972
From what you asked, I figured
density slicing might do the trick.

351
00:19:49,972 --> 00:19:51,002
What's that?

352
00:19:51,002 --> 00:19:55,377
It's when you take each scale of gray
and you print it as pure black and white.

353
00:19:56,423 --> 00:19:58,290
Is that the best you can do, Ray?

354
00:19:58,290 --> 00:20:00,558
Matter of fact, I did better.

355
00:20:02,189 --> 00:20:03,993
And better.

356
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:06,903
Better.

357
00:20:09,946 --> 00:20:13,045
So that's how Washington
knew the runner.

358
00:20:16,866 --> 00:20:18,360
Washington hung with a small-time

359
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:21,657
heroin dealer called the runner
in the early '70s.

360
00:20:21,657 --> 00:20:24,174
We checked juvie records
in the court history database.

361
00:20:24,174 --> 00:20:26,111
Used the tattoo as an identifying mark.

362
00:20:26,111 --> 00:20:28,612
Meet the real Joe Washington.

363
00:20:28,612 --> 00:20:31,950
17 years old, arrested for selling smack.

364
00:20:31,950 --> 00:20:34,236
Gave the arresting officer a false name.

365
00:20:34,236 --> 00:20:38,192
That's why police background
check missed it.

366
00:20:38,192 --> 00:20:40,586
No North Carolina orphanage?

367
00:20:40,586 --> 00:20:41,910
Fairy tale.

368
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:43,333
He grew up in raymond jennings.

369
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:46,262
Straightens out, starts flying right,
joins the military.

370
00:20:46,262 --> 00:20:47,701
Then the police academy.

371
00:20:47,701 --> 00:20:49,175
Gets married, and...

372
00:20:49,175 --> 00:20:50,722
we know the rest.

373
00:20:50,722 --> 00:20:54,223
So Washington buried who
he was from everyone.

374
00:20:54,426 --> 00:20:56,474
Even his wife?

375
00:20:57,141 --> 00:20:59,655
I never knew those things about him.

376
00:20:59,655 --> 00:21:03,315
He never told you where
he really came from?

377
00:21:06,193 --> 00:21:10,300
There were other things he was
hiding from you, weren't there?

378
00:21:11,190 --> 00:21:13,154
Someone robbed you, Diane...

379
00:21:13,154 --> 00:21:16,089
of your husband, of your child.

380
00:21:16,089 --> 00:21:19,058
don't you think he should pay?

381
00:21:20,766 --> 00:21:25,854
Everybody wanted to remember him
as this golden boy...

382
00:21:25,854 --> 00:21:28,345
great cop...

383
00:21:28,345 --> 00:21:30,839
great husband.

384
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:34,133
I didn't want to rain on their parade.

385
00:21:34,133 --> 00:21:35,794
By doing what?

386
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:38,011
I knew he was...

387
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:42,363
he was involved with somebody else.

388
00:21:42,363 --> 00:21:45,191
Married less than a year
and already cheating.

389
00:21:45,191 --> 00:21:47,371
What a joke.

390
00:21:50,953 --> 00:21:53,803
One afternoon,
he went out to the shooting range,

391
00:21:53,803 --> 00:21:57,649
and I needed something from the store,
so I called him.

392
00:21:57,649 --> 00:22:00,784
He wasn't there.
He never showed up.

393
00:22:00,784 --> 00:22:02,529
When he came home that night,

394
00:22:02,529 --> 00:22:07,996
I said,
"hey baby, how was target practice?"

395
00:22:07,996 --> 00:22:10,630
And he said, fine.

396
00:22:10,848 --> 00:22:13,183
It was fine.

397
00:22:13,976 --> 00:22:15,054
I'm sorry.

398
00:22:15,054 --> 00:22:17,778
He'd go out two,
maybe three times a month.

399
00:22:17,778 --> 00:22:19,825
One day I followed him...

400
00:22:31,672 --> 00:22:33,006
Sammy.

401
00:22:33,771 --> 00:22:35,485
It's me.

402
00:22:47,164 --> 00:22:49,281
Her name was Sammy?

403
00:22:49,433 --> 00:22:53,629
Yes. / And she lived at
the raymond jennings projects?

404
00:22:54,027 --> 00:22:56,087
Did you ever confront Joe about her?

405
00:22:56,087 --> 00:23:00,517
I was 20 years old and pregnant.
What was the point?

406
00:23:00,517 --> 00:23:03,118
And you never told the
assigned detective this?

407
00:23:03,118 --> 00:23:04,503
Or even butch?

408
00:23:04,503 --> 00:23:07,431
Like I said, what was the point?

409
00:23:07,602 --> 00:23:11,151
I always wanted to
go back there one day...

410
00:23:11,151 --> 00:23:14,327
meet her face to face,

411
00:23:14,327 --> 00:23:16,769
but I never did.

412
00:23:30,791 --> 00:23:35,006
Heads up. You never know when
a TV might fall out of a window.

413
00:23:40,058 --> 00:23:41,511
Samuela?

414
00:23:41,511 --> 00:23:44,413
This must be the girl who drove
Washington and runner apart.

415
00:23:44,413 --> 00:23:46,386
Looks like our sammy.

416
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:52,942
Think she's still here?

417
00:23:52,942 --> 00:23:54,572
After all these years?

418
00:23:54,572 --> 00:23:58,930
In these projects,
where you're born is where you die.

419
00:24:06,818 --> 00:24:09,009
We're looking for Samuela Robbins?

420
00:24:09,009 --> 00:24:11,824
Yes, I am she.

421
00:24:12,037 --> 00:24:13,844
You're miss Samuela?

422
00:24:13,844 --> 00:24:16,762
Yes. I said that already.

423
00:24:18,944 --> 00:24:21,286
Detectives Rush and Jeffries.

424
00:24:21,286 --> 00:24:23,942
- Could we come in?
- I'd rather you not, thank you.

425
00:24:23,942 --> 00:24:26,759
Did you know a Joe Washington,
Miss Samuela?

426
00:24:26,759 --> 00:24:28,334
You here about Joe?

427
00:24:28,334 --> 00:24:31,559
You should have said so! Come in.

428
00:24:34,116 --> 00:24:36,960
Joe grew up on this very floor.

429
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:41,585
Why, he took care of Sammy
ever since they were kids.

430
00:24:41,585 --> 00:24:43,263
Sammy?

431
00:24:43,263 --> 00:24:46,255
My granddaughter, Samantha.

432
00:24:48,551 --> 00:24:50,228
They grew up together?

433
00:24:50,228 --> 00:24:52,491
Like brother and sister.

434
00:24:52,491 --> 00:24:55,699
He'd bring her back from
school every day.

435
00:24:55,699 --> 00:24:58,183
Real protective.

436
00:24:59,099 --> 00:25:03,397
She was all the love
he had in the world.

437
00:25:03,397 --> 00:25:06,310
Do you remember
when you last saw him?

438
00:25:06,655 --> 00:25:10,149
Well, after he moved out,
he used to come by all the time,

439
00:25:10,149 --> 00:25:13,649
bring her toys, take her to the fair.

440
00:25:13,649 --> 00:25:16,172
Why, on that night he...

441
00:25:16,388 --> 00:25:19,044
the night he what? / Oh...

442
00:25:19,044 --> 00:25:20,553
no, I..I don't know.

443
00:25:20,553 --> 00:25:23,180
The night he was killed.
Isn't that what you mean?

444
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:25,212
No. I don't know anything.

445
00:25:25,212 --> 00:25:26,530
I don't.

446
00:25:26,530 --> 00:25:30,375
Joe loved your granddaughter,
like his own blood, didn't he?

447
00:25:30,375 --> 00:25:32,338
Yes, he did.

448
00:25:32,338 --> 00:25:36,448
And he came here the night
he was killed, didn't he?

449
00:25:37,941 --> 00:25:39,982
Yes, he did.

450
00:25:45,956 --> 00:25:47,228
Joe?

451
00:25:47,906 --> 00:25:49,136
He think he owns me.

452
00:25:49,136 --> 00:25:50,249
Owns Sammy!

453
00:25:50,249 --> 00:25:51,401
What's wrong?

454
00:25:51,401 --> 00:25:53,466
I thought Sammy was in her room.

455
00:25:53,466 --> 00:25:55,541
Oh, she's messing with runner,
takes him them drugs.

456
00:25:55,541 --> 00:25:58,054
You know that, Mrs. Samuela?

457
00:25:58,240 --> 00:26:02,796
I... she won't listen to me,
and I can't keep her in the house all day.

458
00:26:02,796 --> 00:26:04,714
I'm sorry, Miss Samuela.

459
00:26:04,714 --> 00:26:06,564
I know it ain't your fault.

460
00:26:06,564 --> 00:26:09,272
It's just the way things go around here.

461
00:26:09,630 --> 00:26:12,568
Now it's my turn to take care of Sammy.

462
00:26:12,568 --> 00:26:14,083
You know we talked about this.

463
00:26:14,083 --> 00:26:15,577
You know she gots to get out of here

464
00:26:15,577 --> 00:26:18,791
if she's ever going to
have a chance for a life.

465
00:26:31,822 --> 00:26:33,788
That night Joe was killed,

466
00:26:33,788 --> 00:26:37,641
and Sammy...
it was difficult, you understand?

467
00:26:37,641 --> 00:26:40,609
No mother, no father,
just me and Joe.

468
00:26:40,609 --> 00:26:43,486
And then he was gone.

469
00:26:43,486 --> 00:26:47,067
So why didn't you come forward
when Joe was murdered?

470
00:26:47,067 --> 00:26:50,379
There was nothing
I could do to bring him back.

471
00:26:51,005 --> 00:26:52,616
And Sammy..

472
00:26:52,616 --> 00:26:53,874
where is she?

473
00:26:53,874 --> 00:26:56,931
I haven't seen her in over 20 years.

474
00:26:56,931 --> 00:27:02,296
The drugs, they kind of took her over
when Joe died.

475
00:27:02,296 --> 00:27:04,397
Did you know someone...

476
00:27:04,397 --> 00:27:06,736
called the runner?

477
00:27:06,928 --> 00:27:09,545
Joe's best friend.

478
00:27:09,692 --> 00:27:11,536
Mason Tucker.

479
00:27:11,536 --> 00:27:16,058
They went to the catholic
school together, ran track.

480
00:27:16,357 --> 00:27:18,941
So that's why the nickname.

481
00:27:25,657 --> 00:27:29,008
Long way from raymond jennings,
aren't you, Mason?

482
00:27:31,250 --> 00:27:32,974
Can I help you?

483
00:27:33,476 --> 00:27:36,982
Detectives Rush and Jeffries.
Homicide.

484
00:27:37,778 --> 00:27:39,873
We just had a few questions.

485
00:27:39,873 --> 00:27:42,248
About Joe Washington?

486
00:27:42,732 --> 00:27:44,437
Your homie from high school?

487
00:27:44,437 --> 00:27:47,081
Your little drug-running buddy?

488
00:27:48,992 --> 00:27:50,723
I knew Joe.

489
00:27:50,723 --> 00:27:52,036
What's your point?

490
00:27:52,036 --> 00:27:55,659
Night he was murdered, we got witnesses
in the projects saying you two had a fight.

491
00:27:55,659 --> 00:27:58,256
I don't remember no fight.

492
00:27:58,256 --> 00:28:00,037
'Course not.

493
00:28:00,037 --> 00:28:01,665
Remember what you were fighting about?

494
00:28:01,665 --> 00:28:04,379
I'll say it again, I don't remember.

495
00:28:04,773 --> 00:28:06,817
How about Sammy?

496
00:28:06,817 --> 00:28:09,130
Do you remember her?

497
00:28:10,814 --> 00:28:13,593
- Your point being?
- The girl had a lot of problems,

498
00:28:13,593 --> 00:28:16,583
and from what I hear,
you had something to do with it.

499
00:28:17,053 --> 00:28:22,361
Whatever problems Sammy had
were Joe's doing, not mine.

500
00:28:22,928 --> 00:28:24,520
That's not what I hear.

501
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:26,920
I hear it was all on you, Mason.

502
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:30,786
Then I suggest you check
the hospital records yourself.

503
00:28:30,786 --> 00:28:33,904
He was the one who brought
her in, not me.

504
00:28:34,997 --> 00:28:39,984
Now, if you don't have anything else,
I'd like to enjoy my afternoon.

505
00:28:40,514 --> 00:28:42,616
Oh, uh, one last question.

506
00:28:42,616 --> 00:28:46,582
How does one go from
selling smack to selling jags?

507
00:28:47,439 --> 00:28:50,403
Children do dumb things.

508
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:54,622
I'm sure you did, too, detective Rush.

509
00:28:54,622 --> 00:28:57,268
That isn't who I am now.

510
00:28:59,304 --> 00:29:01,952
Sammy was like
a little sister to Washington.

511
00:29:01,952 --> 00:29:03,475
He felt responsible for her,

512
00:29:03,475 --> 00:29:08,405
so he flips when she starts muling drugs
for Mason Tucker.

513
00:29:09,291 --> 00:29:10,496
The night of the murder, Washington

514
00:29:10,496 --> 00:29:14,466
hears a radio call about drug activity
at the raymond jennings projects.

515
00:29:14,466 --> 00:29:16,288
